From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude Fable 5 <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date: Thu, 23 Jul 2026 17:30:00 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] util: do not preallocate alloc cache regional blocks

Every worker alloc cache preallocated max_reg_blocks (100) regional
blocks of 16384 bytes at alloc_init, 1.6 MB per libunbound context
before the first query. The preallocation only reduces contention on
the super alloc under threading; in a single-threaded embedding the
blocks are pure startup cost, and on wasm the linear memory they force
can never be returned.

Allocate regional blocks on demand instead, and keep at most 10 on the
free list, enough for a resolution's steady state of mesh query states.
---

--- a/util/alloc.c
+++ b/util/alloc.c
@@ -113,13 +113,13 @@
 	alloc->last_id -= 1; 			/* for compiler portability. */
 	alloc->last_id |= alloc->next_id;
 	alloc->next_id += 1;			/* because id=0 is special. */
-	alloc->max_reg_blocks = 100;
+	alloc->max_reg_blocks = 10;
 	alloc->num_reg_blocks = 0;
 	alloc->reg_list = NULL;
 	alloc->cleanup = NULL;
 	alloc->cleanup_arg = NULL;
 	if(alloc->super)
-		prealloc_blocks(alloc, alloc->max_reg_blocks);
+		prealloc_blocks(alloc, 0);
 	if(!alloc->super) {
 		lock_quick_init(&alloc->lock);
 		lock_protect(&alloc->lock, alloc, sizeof(*alloc));
